loud.name: Verellen 6x12 Guitar Cabinet For Sale/trade
loud.description: This cab is sounds as fantastic as it is huge. As much as I would love to keep it, it really just doesn't make sense for me to keep it any longer.It's loaded with a pair of Celestion Creambacks on the top, and an x pattern of G12H100s and Vintage 30s on the bottom. It's wired for an 8 ohm load.While the cab is in far from perfect cosmetic condition, as you can see in the pictures, it's in perfectly sound physical shape, and it looks great from the front.This cabinet is a real presence at gigs (whenever we get around to having those again) and would really work well for a stoner or doom band that's going for a Sleep/High on Fire-esque stage presence. It also acts as its own monitor in a sense, as the top speakers are so close to ear level that you should never really have an issue hearing yourself.I've used this cab with a lot of different amps, and it makes each one sound amazing. It's also a very loud cab, and it can handle just about anything you can throw at it. I'm honestly sad to see it go, but I would rather sell it to someone that will use it than to have it sit in my studio.The cab comes with casters. I can't remember the exact dimensions off the top of my head, but its something like 56 tall, 32 wide and between 12 and 14 deep. Point is that this won't fit in every car - just something to be aware of.I'm open to trades. I like cool guitars - something metal oriented with a floyd, or a jazzmaster... try your luck. Not into traditional  strats or teles though. I also love amps. let me know what you have, it may be just what I'm looking for.

loud.name: Fender Concert 2-Channel 60-Watt 1x12" Guitar Combo 1981 - 1987
loud.description: Fender Concert 2-channel 60-watt 1x12 amplifier. This amp has been my go-to amplifier for a couple of years now for gigging and rehearsal. Gets loud, and has a great sound. The overdrive channel is my favorite part of this amplifier because it allowed me to dial in a bit of dirt at lower volumes for small venues. However, these amps are famously revered for their normal channel. Many many players love the clean channel and claim the overdrive is less than desirable, so I supposed everything is subjective.I'm selling it because I've somehow acquired four amplifiers (gasp), and I need to thin out the herd. As best I can tell, this amp was built between 1981 and 1987. It was part of the Rivera era at Fender. The amp has been good to me over the last couple years, but it's time to release it into the wild.Asking $700, or best offer. Amp has caster wheels which is great for gigging. I will also throw in a Mesa Boogie slip cover.
